content: Hi all, is there still an active Sensitive Data Working Group? https://www.gdcc.io/working-groups/sensitive-data.html
It looks like there was a meeting in Feb 2025: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Hv-nyQkzCoofe7VFJLm6SLamMbGD4oZNrB4ty7Wenk0/edit?usp=sharing
@Ceilyn Boyd @Amber Leahey @Rachel Fernandez @Philipp Conzett do you know the status of the group?
Hi everyone! We have been meeting, just not very regularly. @Courtney Mumma did you want to propose a topic and we can set up a time for the working group to reconvene?

At DataverseNO, we might have two possible topics we could present / introduce to: 1) our current work on enhancing our guidelines on data privacy, which ultimately should result in depositors be guided through a set of questions to assess whether the data they are planning to deposit comply with legal requirements and ethical guidelines; 2) a proposal we are working on for funding to establish a national repository for qualitative data.
Hi all-- sorry to go silent on this. I'll mention to the TDR Steering Committee that you're willing to reconvene and also note the topics that Philipp added to the discussion
